# Public-safe Codex config example.
#
# Do not symlink this over ~/.codex/config.toml without reviewing it first.
# Codex stores machine-specific project trust entries in the live config file,
# and those paths do not belong in this public dotfiles repository.
#
# Keep secrets, bearer token env values, private MCP endpoints, account IDs,
# and personal project paths out of this file.

# Named profiles are separate files, not inline tables. For a read-only
# profile, copy readonly.config.toml.example to
# ~/.codex/readonly.config.toml and launch with `codex --profile readonly`.
